496. Next Greater Element I
Problem

You are given two arrays:

nums1 (subset of nums2)
nums2

For each element in nums1, find the first greater element to its right in nums2.

If no greater element exists, return -1.

Example 1
Input:
nums1 = [4,1,2]
nums2 = [1,3,4,2]

Output:
[-1,3,-1]
Example 2
Input:
nums1 = [2,4]
nums2 = [1,2,3,4]

Output:
[3,-1]
Key Observation

We need to find the Next Greater Element (NGE) on the right.

Possible approaches:

Brute Force
Better (Precompute using nested loops + HashMap)
Monotonic Stack + HashMap (Most Optimal)

Approach 1: Brute Force
Intuition

For every element in nums1:

Find its position in nums2.
Scan towards the right.
Return the first greater element.
Java
class Solution {

    public int[] nextGreaterElement(int[] nums1, int[] nums2) {

        int[] ans = new int[nums1.length];

        for (int i = 0; i < nums1.length; i++) {

            int index = 0;

            while (nums2[index] != nums1[i])
                index++;

            ans[i] = -1;

            for (int j = index + 1; j < nums2.length; j++) {

                if (nums2[j] > nums2[index]) {

                    ans[i] = nums2[j];
                    break;
                }
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
}

