Approach 3: Monotonic Stack + HashMap (Most Optimal)
Intuition

Maintain a Monotonic Decreasing Stack.

Whenever the current number is greater than the stack top,

the current number is the Next Greater Element of the stack top.

Store the mapping in a HashMap.

Finally, replace each value in nums1 using the map.

Algorithm
Traverse nums2

↓

Current > Stack Top

↓

Pop Stack

↓

Current becomes Next Greater

↓

Store in HashMap

↓

Push Current

Remaining stack elements

↓

No Next Greater

↓

Answer = -1
Java (Your Code)
class Solution {

    public int[] nextGreaterElement(int[] nums1, int[] nums2) {

        Map<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();

        Stack<Integer> st = new Stack<>();

        for (int num : nums2) {

            while (!st.isEmpty() && st.peek() < num)
                map.put(st.pop(), num);

            st.push(num);
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < nums1.length; i++) {

            nums1[i] = map.getOrDefault(nums1[i], -1);
        }

        return nums1;
    }
}

